Welcome

Lancaster Investment Management is an investment group based in
London and founded in 2007. Lancaster began trading in January 2008
and runs a European Fundamental Equity strategy, managed by Matthew
Wood.
We are a small team of experienced individuals and strive to
create a culture where challenge and debate are expected and
encouraged.
We aim to generate investment returns that are uncorrelated with
equity markets through the investment cycle, thereby allowing us to
compound returns for our investors over long periods of time.
 










Disclaimer
Privacy
Accessibility
Pillar 3 Disclosure
Stewardship Code

LANCASTER INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT LLP IS REGISTERED IN ENGLAND NUMBER OC330805 AND IS AUTHORISED AND REGULATED BY THE FINANCIAL CONDUCT AUTHORITY


 




]> 

	
	Investment Approach







 












         Home
      PhilosophyInvestment ApproachInvestorsContact Us


























Investment Approach

Lancaster manages European Fundamental Equity strategies with a
large cap bias.
Valuation alone is not a sufficient pre-cursor to investment;
each investment must have a clear investment thesis that is
differentiated from the market view.
Stock selection is deeply fundamental with key attention paid to
the supply side dynamics within an industry, and the track record
of cash generation and capital deployment within a business.
Portfolio construction and risk management are critical to the
investment process and are designed to provide duration to allow
individual stock returns to drive fund performance.












